00:13:30.960 --> 00:13:35.920
Thirteen Ghosts did not receive critical acclaim&nbsp;
when it was released. And I get that. It has huge&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:40.960
expositional dump outs, and sometimes jumps from&nbsp;
one thing to another in order to do what it wants&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:40.960 --> 00:13:45.520
rather than doing what makes sense. A couple of&nbsp;
examples of this would be Dennis’s costume change,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:45.520 --> 00:13:50.400
or the inconsistent way they utilized the glasses&nbsp;
- you can’t see the ghosts without the glasses,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:50.400 --> 00:13:53.600
but even when they’re on they&nbsp;
seem to blink in and out. Also,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:57.760
people seem to be unaffected by noises the&nbsp;
ghosts make or being physically manipulated&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:57.760 --> 00:14:02.000
by the ghosts until they put glasses on, but&nbsp;
then don’t always need to have the glasses&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:06.080
on for these things to take effect. The&nbsp;
movie is inconsistent with its own rules

00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:11.040
Even so, this film is mostly here to have fun and&nbsp;
I can see why it is now so highly regarded as a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:11.040 --> 00:14:15.120
cult favorite. If you were younger when you caught&nbsp;
this one, it would be like a visual carnival for&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:15.120 --> 00:14:20.240
the senses. It has a Mummy/Tomb Raider vibe and&nbsp;
comes across like a Disney Haunted Mansion movie,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:20.240 --> 00:14:26.080
